        "comments": "and(p, q) returns true iff both p and q are true. Evaluation is strict in both arguments at the primitive level; for short-circuiting behavior, use ifElse. Total. Corresponds to Haskell's (&&) :: Bool -> Bool -> Bool (but without short-circuit evaluation).",
