        "comments": "ifElse(p, t, f) returns t if p is true, or f if p is false. The unselected branch is not necessarily evaluated; ifElse is the standard way to express short-circuiting boolean logic and branching in Hydra. Total. Corresponds to Haskell's if/then/else.",
